The paper deals with the problem of camera relocalization, which is a subfield of computer vision. The use of multiple modalities, such as image and depth, suggests that the paper may belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The attention-based fusion and variational Product-of-Experts (PoE) joint encoder suggest that the paper may also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category, as these techniques are commonly used in robotics research. The use of deep learning and importance sampling suggests that the paper may belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The end-to-end framework and the focus on accuracy suggest that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the use of multimodal inputs suggests that the paper may belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
